  "Notes": [
    {
      "Text": "Security update for MozillaFirefox",
      "Title": "Topic",
      "Type": "Summary"
    },
    {
      "Text": "This update for MozillaFirefox fixes the following issues:\n\n- Firefox Extended Support Release 128.9.0 ESR MFSA 2025-22 (bsc#1240083):\n  * CVE-2025-3028: Use-after-free triggered by XSLTProcessor\n  * CVE-2025-3029: URL Bar Spoofing via non-BMP Unicode characters\n  * CVE-2025-3030: Memory safety bugs fixed in Firefox 137, Thunderbird 137,\n    Firefox ESR 128.9, and Thunderbird 128.9\n",
      "Title": "Details",
      "Type": "General"
    },
    {
